As Hydras gives his command a wide door slid open revealing a hallway.
&quot;This way.&quot; Came the voice of Breakout, his voice crisp and no
nonsense.&quot;Tankor, send a few of your drones with them to be sure they
get into no mishcief on the way.&quot;

Tankor nodded once, &quot;Sir.&quot; he said in agreement. He gestured to Hydras
as the drones began to lead him down the hall.

&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; hydras started to walk ready for anything while he send a secret mesage to
&gt; MAxima &quot;Be ready, I have a bad feelinga bout this&quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

As Hydras began to walk the door behind him slid shut, plunging him
and his three companions into near darkness for a moment.

&lt;BZZZZT!!&gt; &lt;BZZZZT!&gt; It would also seem that any communications have
been cut off. At the moment it would seem that Hydras is unable to
communicate with the outside, and that would of course include Maxima
as well as Injector and the others.

As this happened at the far end of the hall a door opened and a voice
could be heard as Hydras approached, &quot;Well well My dear Hydras I could
not have you talking about anything behind our backs now could I?&quot;

The voice is  genteel yet sarcastic as it spoke, &quot;It is so good to see
you have made it, you and your . . . um friends there.&quot;

As Hydras got to the door he could see the interior of what would
appear to be a large room, monitors and computer stations lining the
walls. A tall figure hovered near the center of the room, next to what
would at first glance appear to be a throne. The figure seemed to be
draped in shadows, its dark armor almost exuding cold darkness and
threatening evil. It floated a few inches from the floor, helicoptor
type blades spinning at its shoulder blades were holding it aloft. Its
cold red optics turned to look at Hydras as he, inferno, Buzzsaw and
Terrorgator came to the door.

However it is obvious that it was the figure on the throne itself that
had been doing the talking, and the throne turned and the figure of
Cryotek turned to greet Hydra, &quot;It has been a long time, yesss.&quot;

